<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🎮 RB005 Week 8 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Launch &amp; Showcase — Publish and Present · <strong>Course:</strong> Dream Game Studio · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This is it — <strong>launch week</strong>! You publish your game as <strong>Public</strong> and present it like a real game studio.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the situation. Before it happens for real, circle or write your answer.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Your game is published and set to <strong>Public</strong>. Your classmate searches its title on Roblox from their own house.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Can your classmate find and play your game? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<blockquote>
<p>Your game is still set to <strong>Private</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Can a stranger play it? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows the clean launch setup first, then a broken version of the same idea. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the problem.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — Everyone in class should be able to join your game today.</p>
<pre><code>-- clean
Game Settings → Permissions → Public
</code></pre>
<pre><code>-- buggy
Game Settings → Permissions → Private
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? What happens when your classmates try to join?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — Players should start with <strong>0 coins</strong> and earn them by playing.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
local coins = Instance.new(&quot;IntValue&quot;)
coins.Name = &quot;Coins&quot;
coins.Value = 0
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
local coins = Instance.new(&quot;IntValue&quot;)
coins.Name = &quot;Coins&quot;
coins.Value = 999
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Why is starting with 999 coins a problem on launch day?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>To let everyone play your game, one word is missing. Fill it in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code>To launch, set your game to ____ in Game Settings.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>Public</code> · <code>Private</code> · <code>Paused</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Publish your game as <strong>Public</strong>, then plan your showcase here. Send a photo or video of your live game page, then write your plan. Use these sentence starters — write 2 or 3 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My game is called … and you play it by …</p>
<p>The hardest bug I fixed was …</p>
<p>Next, I would build …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>This week your video <strong>IS</strong> the presentation! Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) and present your game like a real game studio. Try to use these words: <strong>publish</strong>, <strong>public</strong>, <strong>bug</strong>, <strong>script</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Say your game's name and show the title screen.</li>
<li>Play your game on camera and show how to win.</li>
<li>Tell your hardest bug story.</li>
<li>Say what you would build next.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
